  "prompt": "Will a magnet stick to copper?",
  "response": "No, a magnet will not stick to copper. Copper is not ferromagnetic, meaning it does not have magnetic properties like iron, nickel, or cobalt, which are materials that magnets can attract. Instead, copper is diamagnetic; when exposed to a magnetic field, it creates an induced magnetic field in the opposite direction, but this effect is very weak and does not cause the magnet to stick to copper.",
